---
<Site
  title="Licensing — Thailand Liveability Index"
  description="How TLI's code, data, and trademark are licensed. Public dataset is CC BY-NC 4.0; commercial use is reserved and not currently licensed."
  locale="en"
  canonicalPath="/en/licensing/"
  ogImage="/og/licensing.png"
>
  <main class="container" style="max-width:760px; padding-block: var(--sp-7);">
    <Breadcrumbs locale="en" items={[{ label: 'Licensing' }]} />
    <h1>Licensing</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      The Thailand Liveability Index is built around three distinct
      licensing layers — code, public dataset, and trademark — each
      governed by its own terms. This page explains the boundary and
      points to the canonical license texts.
    </p>

    <h2>Code — MIT</h2>
    <p>
      The TypeScript, Astro, Python, and shell source code in this
      repository is licensed under the
      <a href="https://github.com/ReynoldsWJ55/thailand-liveability-index/blob/main/LICENSE-CODE">MIT License</a>.
      You can use, modify, and redistribute the code freely, including
      commercially, with attribution.
    </p>

    <h2>Public dataset — CC BY-NC 4.0</h2>
    <p>
      The methodology document, indicator definitions, scoring algorithm,
      data outputs (province-level scores, indicator meta), and other
      non-code content are licensed under
      <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/">Creative
      Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0)</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Free use cases under CC BY-NC 4.0:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Academic research, theses, and peer-reviewed publication</li>
      <li>Journalism and editorial coverage</li>
      <li>Personal, civic, and educational use</li>
      <li>Thai government and public-sector use</li>
      <li>Non-profit organizations whose use is non-commercial</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Commercial use — reserved, not currently licensed</h2>
    <p>
      The Thailand Liveability Index is a non-commercial open-data
      project. <strong>Commercial use of the methodology, data outputs,
      indicator definitions, or any derived material is currently
      reserved and is not licensed.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      A commercial-licensing pathway may be made available at a future
      date. Whether it ever becomes available is contingent and
      uncertain. There is currently no commercial offering, no
      published pricing, and no active commercial-licensing service.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you may have an interest in any future commercial licensing
      should it ever become available, you may send an informational
      expression of interest to
      <a href="mailto:licensing@thailandliveabilityindex.com">licensing@thailandliveabilityindex.com</a>.
      Such expressions are recorded for awareness only. They are not
      commercial transactions, do not create a contract, do not
      commit either party, and do not initiate a commercial
      relationship.
    </p>
    <p class="meta">
      Context for the reservation:
      <a href="https://github.com/ReynoldsWJ55/thailand-liveability-index/blob/main/LICENSE-COMMERCIAL.md">LICENSE-COMMERCIAL.md</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Trademark</h2>
    <p>
      The names "Thailand Liveability Index" and "TLI", together with
      any associated visual marks, are trademarks of the project
      maintainer. The MIT and CC BY-NC 4.0 licenses do not grant
      rights in the project's name or marks. See
      <a href="https://github.com/ReynoldsWJ55/thailand-liveability-index/blob/main/TRADEMARK.md">TRADEMARK.md</a>
      for the trademark boundary and the "if you have any doubt, ask"
      contact.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party data</h2>
    <p>
      Underlying source data used in producing TLI scores is licensed
      by the original data providers — Thai government agencies,
      OpenAQ, ACLED, OpenStreetMap, and others. TLI's CC BY-NC 4.0
      license applies only to the methodology, indicator definitions,
      and aggregated output produced by this project. Users
      redistributing underlying source data should consult and comply
      with each source's license terms directly.
    </p>

    <p class="meta" style="margin-top:var(--sp-7);">
      This page reflects the licensing posture as of 2026-05-01.
      Last updated: 2026-05-01.
    </p>
  </main>
</Site>
